Q. Where do you sleep - A. In the next room to the prisoner. I went to bed a little after eleven o'clock, and he was in his room then for I heard him cough; he could not have gone out from the time he came in until I went to bed, or I must have heard him. He sleeps in the front room, and we supped in the front room. Mr. Shannon went away about eleven o'clock;
Eliza Sinclair
let him out; she brought me the key about a quarter past eleven o'clock, and it was not out of my possession until the morning.
